{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":680,"text":"Here's a question for you:"},{"time":3440,"text":"how many different scents\ndo you think you can smell,"},{"time":6600,"text":"and maybe even identify with accuracy?"},{"time":10800,"text":"100?"},{"time":12840,"text":"300?"},{"time":15080,"text":"1,000?"},{"time":18280,"text":"One study estimates that humans can\ndetect up to one trillion different odors."},{"time":24280,"text":"A trillion."},{"time":25920,"text":"It's hard to imagine,"},{"time":27760,"text":"but your nose has the molecular\nmachinery to make it happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32960,"text":"Olfactory receptors --"},{"time":34760,"text":"tiny scent detectors --"},{"time":36720,"text":"are packed into your nose,"},{"time":38680,"text":"each one patiently waiting\nto be activated by the odor,"},{"time":42120,"text":"or ligand,"},{"time":43440,"text":"that it's been assigned to detect."},{"time":46520,"text":"It turns out we humans,\nlike all vertebrates,"},{"time":49640,"text":"have lots of olfactory receptors."},{"time":52800,"text":"In fact, more of our DNA is devoted\nto genes for different olfactory receptors"},{"time":59560,"text":"than for any other type of protein."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63240,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":65640,"text":"Could olfactory receptors\nbe doing something else"},{"time":68960,"text":"in addition to allowing us to smell?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73840,"text":"In 1991, Linda Buck and Richard Axel\nuncovered the molecular identity"},{"time":78920,"text":"of olfactory receptors --"},{"time":80440,"text":"work which ultimately\nled to a Nobel Prize."},{"time":84560,"text":"At the time,"},{"time":85800,"text":"we all assumed that these receptors\nwere only found in the nose."},{"time":90480,"text":"However, about a year or so later,"},{"time":92720,"text":"a report emerged of an olfactory\nreceptor expressed in a tissue"},{"time":97240,"text":"other than the nose."},{"time":99360,"text":"And then another such report emerged,"},{"time":102040,"text":"and another."},{"time":103880,"text":"We now know that these receptors\nare found all over the body,"},{"time":107960,"text":"including in some pretty\nunexpected places --"},{"time":111920,"text":"in muscle,"},{"time":113560,"text":"in kidneys,"},{"time":115160,"text":"lungs"},{"time":116720,"text":"and blood vessels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118520,"text":"But what are they doing there?"},{"time":123760,"text":"Well, we know that olfactory receptors\nact as sensitive chemical sensors"},{"time":128479,"text":"in the nose --"},{"time":129720,"text":"that's how they mediate\nour sense of smell."},{"time":132480,"text":"It turns out they also act\nas sensitive chemical sensors"},{"time":136680,"text":"in many other parts of the body."},{"time":139280,"text":"Now, I'm not saying that your liver can\ndetect the aroma of your morning coffee"},{"time":144200,"text":"as you walk into the kitchen."},{"time":146480,"text":"Rather, after you drink\nyour morning coffee,"},{"time":149640,"text":"your liver might use an olfactory receptor"},{"time":152640,"text":"to chemically detect\nthe change in concentration"},{"time":155840,"text":"of a chemical floating\nthrough your bloodstream."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"Many cell types and tissues in the body\nuse chemical sensors,"},{"time":162520,"text":"or chemosensors,"},{"time":164040,"text":"to keep track of the concentration\nof hormones, metabolites"},{"time":168040,"text":"and other molecules,"},{"time":169520,"text":"and some of these chemosensors\nare olfactory receptors."},{"time":175320,"text":"If you are a pancreas or a kidney"},{"time":177200,"text":"and you need a specialized chemical sensor"},{"time":180040,"text":"that will allow you to keep track\nof a specific molecule,"},{"time":183640,"text":"why reinvent the wheel?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":187640,"text":"One of the first examples"},{"time":189400,"text":"of an olfactory receptor\nfound outside the nose"},{"time":192360,"text":"showed that human sperm\nexpress an olfactory receptor,"},{"time":197400,"text":"and that sperm with this receptor\nwill seek out the chemical"},{"time":201720,"text":"that the receptor responds to --"},{"time":203680,"text":"the receptor's ligand."},{"time":205360,"text":"That is, the sperm\nwill swim toward the ligand."},{"time":210240,"text":"This has intriguing implications."},{"time":213440,"text":"Are sperm aided in finding the egg"},{"time":216480,"text":"by sniffing out the area\nwith the highest ligand concentration?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":221600,"text":"I like this example\nbecause it clearly demonstrates"},{"time":224960,"text":"that an olfactory receptor's primary job\nis to be a chemical sensor,"},{"time":230280,"text":"but depending on the context,"},{"time":233200,"text":"it can influence how you perceive a smell,"},{"time":236920,"text":"or in which direction sperm will swim,"},{"time":241600,"text":"and as it turns out,"},{"time":242920,"text":"a huge variety of other processes."},{"time":245920,"text":"Olfactory receptors have been\nimplicated in muscle cell migration,"},{"time":250960,"text":"in helping the lung to sense\nand respond to inhaled chemicals,"},{"time":255000,"text":"and in wound healing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257440,"text":"Similarly, taste receptors once thought\nto be found only in the tongue,"},{"time":262040,"text":"are now known to be expressed\nin cells and tissues throughout the body."},{"time":267160,"text":"Even more surprisingly,"},{"time":269360,"text":"a recent study found"},{"time":270880,"text":"that the light receptors in our eyes\nalso play a role in our blood vessels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278800,"text":"In my lab,"},{"time":280080,"text":"we work on trying to understand the roles\nof olfactory receptors and taste receptors"},{"time":285560,"text":"in the context of the kidney."},{"time":289080,"text":"The kidney is a central\ncontrol center for homeostasis."},{"time":292880,"text":"And to us,"},{"time":294120,"text":"it makes sense that a homeostatic\ncontrol center would be a logical place"},{"time":297920,"text":"to employ chemical sensors."},{"time":301520,"text":"We've identified a number\nof different olfactory and taste receptors"},{"time":305200,"text":"in the kidney,"},{"time":306560,"text":"one of which, olfactory receptor 78,"},{"time":310160,"text":"is known to be expressed\nin cells and tissues"},{"time":313560,"text":"that are important\nin the regulation of blood pressure."},{"time":318280,"text":"When this receptor is deleted in mice,"},{"time":321560,"text":"their blood pressure is low."},{"time":325440,"text":"Surprisingly, this receptor\nwas found to respond"},{"time":328920,"text":"to chemicals called\nshort-chain fatty acids"},{"time":332160,"text":"that are produced by the bacteria\nthat reside in your gut --"},{"time":336000,"text":"your gut microbiota."},{"time":338840,"text":"After being produced\nby your gut microbiota,"},{"time":341560,"text":"these chemicals are absorbed\ninto your bloodstream"},{"time":344400,"text":"where they can then\ninteract with receptors"},{"time":346520,"text":"like olfactory receptor 78,"},{"time":349560,"text":"meaning that the changes\nin metabolism of your gut microbiota"},{"time":354440,"text":"may influence your blood pressure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359840,"text":"Although we've identified a number\nof different olfactory and taste receptors"},{"time":364160,"text":"in the kidney,"},{"time":365440,"text":"we've only just begun\nto tease out their different functions"},{"time":368600,"text":"and to figure out which chemicals\neach of them responds to."},{"time":373240,"text":"Similar investigations lie ahead\nfor many other organs and tissues --"},{"time":377200,"text":"only a small minority of receptors\nhas been studied to date."},{"time":383240,"text":"This is exciting stuff."},{"time":386080,"text":"It's revolutionizing our understanding\nof the scope of influence"},{"time":389640,"text":"for one of the five senses."},{"time":392600,"text":"And it has the potential\nto change our understanding"},{"time":395280,"text":"of some aspects of human physiology."},{"time":399560,"text":"It's still early,"},{"time":400800,"text":"but I think we've picked up on the scent\nof something we're following."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":406120,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":407360,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}